                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.30/14: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harvey</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-12-23T18:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 23, 1921—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 23—4:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>999. French Ambassador orally conveys to me message for you from Briand following
                    meeting of his Cabinet. It contains nothing new, helpful or suggestive. Mere
                    reiteration of French Government insistence upon 330,000 tonnage light craft and
                    90,000 tonnage submarines as proper and necessary for national defense.
                    Nevertheless they were willing to discuss possible modification. To my inquiry
                    whether Briand had indicated degree of possible modification for confidential
                    communication to you he shook his head vaguely. In point of fact he seemed quite
                    destitute of any information approximating definiteness or accuracy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harvey</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
